roundRect

Draws a rounded rectangle using the current state of the canvas. If you omit the last three params, it will draw a rectangle outline with a 5 pixel border radius

roundRect(ctx: CanvasRenderingContext2D, x: Number, y: Number, width: Number, height: Number, radius: Number, fill: Boolean, stroke: Boolean, strokeWidth: Number?)
Parameters
ctx (CanvasRenderingContext2D)
x (Number) The top left x coordinate
y (Number) The top left y coordinate
width (Number) The width of the rectangle
height (Number) The height of the rectangle
radius (Number = 5) The corner radius; It can also be an object to specify different radii for corners
Name Description
radius.tl Number (default 0) Top left
radius.tr Number (default 0) Top right
radius.br Number (default 0) Bottom right
radius.bl Number (default 0) Bottom left
fill (Boolean = false) Whether to fill the rectangle.
stroke (Boolean = true) Whether to stroke the rectangle.
strokeWidth (Number?) The strokeWidth param.
